		<h3>Abilities</h3>	
		Starting Abilities: </br>
		<ol style="1"> 
			<li>Pickpocket – Reach into the troves of the unknowing, and take what you will for your own.</br> 
			Attempt to pick an enemy’s pocket and remove an equipped item. Effectiveness is based on d100 + 2 x EVA bonus. Must be dealt from behind an enemy.</li>  
			
			<li>Charm – Use your sharply crafted wit to distract the weak minded.</br> 
			Capture the attention of an enemy, distracting them from the rest of the party. Enemy is distracted for # of turns equal to CHR bonus. Roll a d6 to determine whether or not the enemy will act hostile to the Thief while charmed (1-4 hostile, 5-6 nonhostile).</li>  
		</ol>	
			Lvl 3: </br>
			<ul> 
				<li>Dirty Tricks – Fair fights are for the dead.</br>  
				Throw sand in target’s eye, dealing basic attack damage. Target must be at least 10 ft from Thief. Target is disoriented for number of turns equal to Thief’s basic power level, and will attack anything within 5 ft. </li>    
			</ul>
